    <title>machine-learning</title>
    <link href="https://staticor.github.io/2019/03/03/machine-learning/"/>
    <id>https://staticor.github.io/2019/03/03/machine-learning/</id>
    <published>2019-03-03T02:23:42.000Z</published>
    <updated>2019-03-03T04:51:13.497Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>假期找了几本关于机器学习的书，将一些比较重要的核心公式整体到这里。</p><h1 id="线性回归"><a href="#线性回归" class="headerlink" title="线性回归"></a>线性回归</h1><h2 id="模型描述"><a href="#模型描述" class="headerlink" title="模型描述"></a>模型描述</h2><p>特征空间假设， 寻找线性系数 $ \theta $ 以希望用一个线性函数逼近目标向量。</p><p>逼近的效果好坏叫做 <strong>Cost Function</strong>， 下面列出的MSE便是其中一种。</p><blockquote><p>Linear Regression</p></blockquote><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\hat y = h_{\theta} (x) =  \theta \cdot x</script><script type="math/tex; mode=display">MSE(x, h_{\theta}) =  \frac{1}{m} \sum_{i=1}^{m} ( \theta^T \cdot x^{(i)} - y^{(i)} )^2</script><h2 id="梯度下降"><a href="#梯度下降" class="headerlink" title="梯度下降"></a>梯度下降</h2><img src="/2019/03/03/machine-learning/sgd.png" title="sgd"><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\Theta^{(next step)} = \Theta - \eta \nabla_\theta MSE( \theta )</script><p>其中 </p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\nabla_\theta MSE( \theta ) = \begin{pmatrix}\frac{\partial}{\partial_{\theta_0}} MSE( \theta ) \\\frac{\partial}{\partial_{\theta_1}} MSE( \theta ) \\\cdots \\\frac{\partial}{\partial_{\theta_n}} MSE( \theta ) \\\end{pmatrix} = \frac{2}{m} X^T (X\Theta - Y)</script><h2 id="带有正则项"><a href="#带有正则项" class="headerlink" title="带有正则项"></a>带有正则项</h2><ul><li>Ridge Regression</li></ul><script type="math/tex; mode=display">J(\theta) = MSE(\theta) + \alpha \frac{1}{2} \sum_{i=1}^{n} \theta_i^2</script><img src="/2019/03/03/machine-learning/ridge.png" title="ridge"><ul><li>LASSO</li></ul><script type="math/tex; mode=display">J(\theta) = MSE(\theta) + \alpha \sum_{i=1}^{n} | \theta_i |</script><ul><li>Elastic Net</li></ul><script type="math/tex; mode=display">J(\theta) = MSE(\theta) + r \alpha \sum_{i=1}^{n} | \theta_i | + \frac{1-r}{2} \alpha  \sum_{i=1}^{n} \theta_i^2</script><figure class="highlight python"><figcaption><span>sklearn-线性回归</span></figcaption><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">from</span> sklearn.linear_model <span class="keyword">import</span> LinearRegression</span><br><span class="line">lr = LinearRegression()</span><br><span class="line">lr.fit(X, y)</span><br><span class="line">lr.intercept_, lr.coef_</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">#mse</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">from</span> sklearn.metrics <span class="keyword">import</span> mean_squared_error</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># sgd</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">from</span> sklearn.linear_model <span class="keyword">import</span> SGDRegressor</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h2 id="对数线性回归-Logistic-Regression"><a href="#对数线性回归-Logistic-Regression" class="headerlink" title="对数线性回归 - Logistic Regression"></a>对数线性回归 - Logistic Regression</h2><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\hat p = h_\theta (x) = \sigma (\theta^T x)</script><p>$ \sigma(t) $ 是Sigmoid函数</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\sigma (t) =  \frac{1}{1 + exp(-t) }</script><p>Logistic Regression cost function (log loss)</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">J(\theta) = - \frac{1}{m} \sum_{i=1}^{m} [y^{(i)} log( { \hat p }^(i) )   +  (1-y^{(i)})log( 1-{\hat p}^i)  ]</script><p>Logistic cost function partial derivatives </p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\frac{\partial}{\partial \theta_j } J(\boldsymbol \theta) = \frac{1}{m} \sum_{i=1}^{m} ( \sigma ( \boldsymbol \theta^T x^i ) -y^i ) x_j^i</script><figure class="highlight python"><figcaption><span>sklearn-Logistic Regression</span></figcaption><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">from</span> sklearn.linear_model <span class="keyword">import</span> LogisticRegression</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">log_reg = LogisticRegression()</span><br><span class="line">log_reg.fit(X, y)</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h2 id="Softmax-Regression"><a href="#Softmax-Regression" class="headerlink" title="Softmax Regression"></a>Softmax Regression</h2><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\widehat p_k = \sigma ( \boldsymbol s(x))_k   = \frac{exp(s_k(\boldsymbol x))}{ \sum_{j=1}^K exp(s_j(\boldsymbol x))}</script>]]></content>
    
